#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000005000033F1"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x010000710000163A"
msgid "The sheets feel at once coarse and clammy against your skin. The bed sags beneath your weight as you stretch out and finally close your eyes..."
msgstr ""
"Sofort fühlt sich das Laken an deiner Haut rau und klamm an. Das Bett sackt unter deinem Gewicht ein, als du dich ausstreckst und endlich die Augen schließt …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A0001256B"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100000500003408"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A00012483"
msgid "The bed is cold and not particularly inviting, but it's yours. The sheets look awful..."
msgstr ""
"Das Bett ist kalt und nicht besonders einladend, aber es ist deins. Das Laken ist in einem furchtbaren Zustand …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000005000033F7"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A00012595"
msgid "Across the room, the heating system hums its soft lullaby. The mattress feels soft and sheets warm. It only takes you moments for the world to fall away..."
msgstr ""
"Sanft summt die Heizungsanlage des Zimmers ihr Schlaflied. Die Matratze fühlt sich weich, das Laken warm an. Es braucht nur einige Augenblicke, bis die Welt für dich verschwindet …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate1/0x0100005A00012595"
msgid "The place feels almost like home now, quiet and dignified around you -- a new life by the seaside. You're incredibly tired. The darkness and warmth come fast. You're falling asleep..."
msgstr ""
"Mittlerweile fühlst du dich hier fast zu Hause, an diesem von stiller Würde umgebenen Ort – ein neues Leben an der Küste. Du bist unglaublich müde. Dunkelheit und Wärme lassen nicht lange auf sich warten. Du schläfst ein …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate2/0x0100005A00012595"
msgid "The bed underneath you is soft, if lumpy. Waves wash the sand underneath the hut, then grow distant to your ear. In the quiet hum of the organic heater, you fall asleep..."
msgstr ""
"Das Bett, auf dem du liegst, ist weich, wenn auch uneben. Wellen überspülen den Sand unter der Hütte, dann rückt der Klang ihres Brausens in immer größere Ferne. Das leise Summen der Heizung wiegt dich in den Schlaf …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x010000030000028A"
msgid "And then sleep doesn't come."
msgstr ""
"Und dann kannst du einfach nicht einschlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000021000023B7"
msgid "The window is fixed, the sheets are new, it's easier to fall asleep than ever before..."
msgstr ""
"Das Fenster wurde repariert, das Bett ist frisch bezogen. Das macht das Einschlafen leichter denn je …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x010000210000124C"
msgid "..."
msgstr ""
"…"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A0001244E"
msgid "The sheets feel at once coarse and clammy against your skin. The bed sags beneath your weight as you stretch out and finally close your eyes..."
msgstr ""
"Sofort fühlt sich das Laken an deiner Haut rau und klamm an. Das Bett sackt unter deinem Gewicht ein, als du dich ausstreckst und endlich die Augen schließt …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A0001243B"
msgid "Crawl in."
msgstr ""
"Du kriechst hinein."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A00012447"
msgid "No time to rest yet. [Leave.]"
msgstr ""
"Du hast noch keine Zeit, dich auszuruhen. [Ende.]"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A00012579"
msgid "The passage of time has not made the sheets any less coarse. The bed sags beneath your weight as you close your eyes and drift off into an uneasy sleep..."
msgstr ""
"Nach der verstrichenen Zeit fühlt sich das Laken nicht weniger rau an. Das Bett sackt unter deinem Gewicht ein, als du die Augen schließt und in einen unruhigen Schlaf gleitest …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate1/0x0100005A00012579"
msgid "The unchanged linens are only getting greasier and greasier every time you crawl among them. Like some wounded animal you close your eyes and ask for sleep. Just some hours of regular sleep, please..."
msgstr ""
"Jedes Mal, wenn du dich mit ihr zudeckst, wird die Bettwäsche dreckiger. Wie ein verletztes Tier schließt du die Augen und bittest um etwas Schlaf. Nur ein paar Stunden ungestörter Schlaf, bitte …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate2/0x0100005A00012579"
msgid "The room behind your closed eyelids is familiar now. The only home you've ever known. Its darkness gathers. The last thing you hear is the wind blowing in through the broken window, then something comes: a kind of sleep..."
msgstr ""
"Mittlerweile ist dir das Zimmer, das hinter deinen geschlossenen Lidern liegt, vertraut. Es ist das einzige Zuhause, das du kennst. Seine Dunkelheit umhüllt dich. Das Letzte, was du hörst, ist der Wind, der durch das kaputte Fenster hereinweht. Dann versinkst du in einer Art Schlaf …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate3/0x0100005A00012579"
msgid "It's not easy, but your bones are *so* tired from what feel like *weeks* of work on the case. You have to try. After what feels like hours, you feel you *might* be sleeping..."
msgstr ""
"Es ist nicht einfach, aber deine Knochen sind <i>so</i> müde von der gefühlt <i>wochenlangen</i> Arbeit am Fall. Du musst es versuchen. Nach gefühlten Stunden denkst du, dass du <i>vielleicht</i> schläfst …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate4/0x0100005A00012579"
msgid "The bed is still cold from the wind blowing in from the broken window. The mattress creaks as you close your eyes and try your hardest to fall asleep..."
msgstr ""
"Das Bett ist immer noch kalt, weil der Wind durch das kaputte Fenster hereinweht. Die Matratze ächzt, als du die Augen schließt und dein Bestes versuchst, um einzuschlafen …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100006B00003D09"
msgid "Across the room, the heating system hums a soft lullaby. The mattress feels soft and sheets warm. After some time you fall into uneasy sleep..."
msgstr ""
"Sanft summt die Heizungsanlage des Zimmers ihr Schlaflied. Die Matratze fühlt sich weich, das Laken warm an. Nach einiger Zeit fällst du in einen unruhigen Schlaf …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000005000033FD"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Tutorial Agent
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x010000210000187C"
msgid "The option to go to sleep becomes available every night after 21.00."
msgstr ""
"Jeden Abend nach 21:00 Uhr hast du die Möglichkeit, schlafen zu gehen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A0001258A"
msgid "The bed is comforting, if a bit run down. Still, you've earned a rest."
msgstr ""
"Das Bett ist bequem, wenn auch etwas heruntergekommen. Trotzdem hast du dir etwas Ruhe verdient."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Alternate1/0x0100005A0001258A"
msgid "The bed is alright. You could sleep here -- later, once night has come. To the sound of waves crashing outside... you've earned it."
msgstr ""
"Das Bett ist in Ordnung. Du könntest hier schlafen – später, wenn es Nacht geworden ist. Während sich draußen die Wellen brechen … Du hast es dir verdient."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100006B00003CFA"
msgid "The day has not made the sheets any less coarse. The bed sags beneath your weight as you close your eyes and fall into uneasy sleep..."
msgstr ""
"Nach diesem Tag fühlt sich das Laken nicht weniger rau an. Das Bett sackt unter deinem Gewicht ein, als du die Augen schließt und in einen unruhigen Schlaf fällst …"

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100005A000124C1"
msgid "The bed is still cold from the broken window, and not too inviting. But it's yours. You've earned it."
msgstr ""
"Wegen des kaputten Fensters ist das Bett immer noch kalt und nicht besonders einladend. Aber es ist deins. Du hast dir deine Ruhe verdient."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000005000033E5"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = You
#. Conversant = Bed
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000005000033EB"
msgid "Go to sleep."
msgstr ""
"Du gehst schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x01000021000023A0"
msgid "The bed's a little nicer now. You could get a good night's sleep here."
msgstr ""
"Das Bett ist nun etwas bequemer. Hier könntest du tief und fest schlafen."

#. Title = DAYCHANGE / TEQUILA BED
#. Description = The dialogue between You and your bed. You can sleep, not sleep, read your ledger.
#. Actor = Bed
#. Conversant = You
msgctxt "Dialogue Text/0x0100002100001245"
msgid "..."
msgstr ""
"…"
